          <source>How to: Set Up Automatic Menu Merging for MDI Applications</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following procedure gives the basic steps for setting up automatic merging in a multiple-document interface (MDI) application with <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To set up automatic menu merging</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create the MDI parent form by setting its <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form.IsMdiContainer%2A&gt;</ph> property to <ph id="ph2">`true`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph> to the MDI parent, setting its <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form.MainMenuStrip%2A&gt;</ph> property to that <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create an MDI child form, and set its <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form.MdiParent%2A&gt;</ph> property to the name of the parent form.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph> to the MDI child form.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the child form, set the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem.Visible%2A&gt;</ph> property of the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph> to <ph id="ph3">`false`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add menu items to the child form's <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph> that you want to merge into the parent form's <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph> when the child form is activated.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem.MergeAction%2A&gt;</ph> property on the menu items in the child form's <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.MenuStrip&gt;</ph> to control how they merge into the parent form.</source>
        </trans-unit>
